t: A Song of degrees of David.
Behold,*p how good and how pleasant it is for brethren to dwell together in unity!
It*p is like the precious ointment upon the head, that ran down upon the beard, even Aaron's beard: that went down to the skirts of his garments;
As*p the dew of Hermon, and as the dew that descended upon the mountains of Zion: for there the Lord*s commanded the blessing, even life for evermore.
